SSL Certificate:

Important Links:
Link1. Procedure to install lets encrypt certificate on Elastic Load Balancer-
https://blog.cloudinvaders.com/installing-a-lets-encrypt-certificate-on-an-elastic-load-balancer/
Link2. Procedure to configure nginx for lets encrypt certificate-
https://www.nginx.com/blog/using-free-ssltls-certificates-from-lets-encrypt-with-nginx/

Procedure to create lets encrypt certificate-
1. Create Certificate using procedure mentioned in link1
2. If you are using Elastic load balancer, Add 443 https listner and provide Create IAM role for the certificate
3. If you are not using Elastic load balancer, Configure Apache or Nginx web server using procedure mentined in the link2 
4. Modify security group to allow https traffic in aws

Procedure to upload lets encrypt certificate on AWS Load Balancers-
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37382741/how-to-renew-letsencrypt-cert-in-aws-load-balancer
https://blog.alejandrocelaya.com/2016/08/16/setup-a-lets-encrypt-certificate-in-a-aws-elastic-load-balancer/

